## Key Contracts You Must Respect (Set by Agent 03)

These are **stable API**. Do not re-derive or rename them.

### Hero intent / decision
- `hero.intent: str` ‚Äî taxonomy label; always non-empty; set via `self.set_intent(hero, label)`
- `hero.last_decision: HeroDecisionRecord | None`
- `hero.get_intent_snapshot(now_ms=None) -> dict` ‚Äî use this for UI/debug reads; no AI imports needed
- `hero.record_decision(action, reason, now_ms, context)` ‚Äî call on meaningful state transitions only

### Intent taxonomy (locked)
```
idle, pursuing_bounty, shopping, returning_to_safety,
engaging_enemy, defending_building, attacking_lair
```

### Combat gating (set by Agent 03 / hero.py)
- `hero.can_attack: bool` ‚Äî hard gate; CombatSystem checks this. You do not set it ‚Äî hero.py sets it from `is_inside_building`.
- Do not add damage or attack code to `ai/basic_ai.py` ‚Äî that lives in `game/systems/combat.py`.

### Stuck signals (set by hero.py / you populate via BasicAI)
- `hero.stuck_active`, `hero.stuck_since_ms`, `hero.last_progress_ms`, `hero.unstuck_attempts`, `hero.stuck_reason`
- Detection + recovery lives in `BasicAI._update_stuck_and_recover()` ‚Äî thresholds imported from `game/sim/hero_guardrails_tunables.py`

### Purchase tracking (v1.3, set by hero.py)
- `hero.last_purchase_ms: int | None` ‚Äî sim-time of most recent successful purchase
- `hero.last_purchase_type: str` ‚Äî "potion", "weapon", "armor"
- Used for Journey trigger; set inside `hero.buy_item()` automatically

### Timebase rule (non-negotiable)
- All sim-time: `game.sim.timebase.now_ms()` (imported as `sim_now_ms`)
- Never: `time.time()`, `pygame.time.get_ticks()` in sim/AI logic
- All AI randomness: `_AI_RNG = get_rng("ai_basic")` ‚Äî never `random.random()`

