## Behavior Architecture (Know This Cold)

### BasicAI state machine flow (per hero per tick)
1. `refresh_intent()` ‚Äî keep intent non-empty
2. `_update_stuck_and_recover()` ‚Äî WK2 stuck detection
3. Priority checks (resting / defend castle / defend home / defend neutral building)
4. LLM consult gate (`should_consult_llm()`)
5. Apply pending LLM decision if ready
6. State dispatch: IDLE ‚Üí `handle_idle()`, MOVING ‚Üí `handle_moving()`, FIGHTING ‚Üí `handle_fighting()`, RETREATING ‚Üí `handle_retreating()`, SHOPPING ‚Üí `handle_shopping()`

### IDLE priority order (inside `handle_idle()`)
1. `maybe_take_bounty()` ‚Äî Majesty-style indirect control lever
2. Shopping check (full HP, has gold, needs potions)
3. Patrol/zone wander (Rangers use `explore()` for black-fog frontier bias)

### Bounty scoring (`score_bounty()`)
- Reward / distance / risk, class-weighted
- Black-fog penalty: `BOUNTY_BLACK_FOG_DISTANCE_PENALTY` multiplier on distance ‚Äî never excludes
- Min-score gate: `0.15` (lowered in v1.3 from 0.5 to fix bounty avoidance)
- Passed `world` from `game_state` for fog visibility check

### Journey behavior (v1.3, post-shopping)
- Triggered in `do_shopping()` ‚Üí `_maybe_start_journey()`
- Conditions: purchased something + full HP + within `journey_trigger_window_ms` + not on cooldown
- Class routing:
  - **Warrior**: 65% chance ‚Üí attack nearest lair; else explore 10‚Äì30 tile fog frontier
  - **Ranger**: explore 6+ tile fog frontier; 25% fallback to lair
  - **Rogue**: short fog step (2‚Äì6 tile frontier, prefer close)
- All uses `_find_black_fog_frontier_tiles()` with configurable `scan_radius`, `min_dist_tiles`, `max_dist_tiles`

### Fallback decision (no-LLM / parse failure)
- `get_fallback_decision(context)` in `ai/prompt_templates.py`
- Deterministic priority: critical health ‚Üí low health in combat ‚Üí can shop ‚Üí enemies nearby ‚Üí idle default
- **Always records decision with `source="fallback"`**

